        <div1 type="summary">
            <p><add hand="#barker">Business in Arkansas Long's expedition.</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p><placeName>Natchitoches </placeName><date when="1819-09-21">Sept 21st 1819</date></p>

<p>Sir I recevd Your letter of the <date when="1819-08-17">l7th of August</date> Last you say you
have had no Letter from me which is strange to me as I have writen
to you several times and inclosed you all the letters that has arived
at this Place&#8212; I have also taken up all the paper you left in that
way viz 1 note of one hundred dollars for <persName>Brian </persName>to <persName>Kempley </persName>one of
$30 to <persName>Burger </persName>and the amount of sugar with <persName>Samprack </persName>[Sampyrac]
and <persName>Butler</persName>s accompt etc</p>

<p>As to the suit Respecting the Boat we had it Put of until next
tirm which will Be in <date n="12-xx-1819">December </date>next as I wrote you Before&#8212; As
to the <persName>Spanish expadition</persName> it has Past its zenath and many of the
<persName>officers </persName>Deserting the cause which I Beleeve was at Best a Bad one
and conducted By Bad men Reports say some things of the<persName> officers
at the Head of affairs</persName> that is not prudent to put on Paper as there
is things of a <persName>femanine </persName>nature involved in it</p>

<p>Adieu</p>

<p><persName>J. H. Bell</persName></p>

<p>there was some of the flour damaged which I had to sell at a
under rate and on credit I had to advance about twenty Dollars
which I have not yet Colected&#8212;</p>

<p>[Addressed:] <persName>Mr S. F. Austin</persName> <placeName>Mount Prairie Arkansas</placeName> <persName>Ty </persName>By
<persName>Morrison</persName></p>

        </div1>
